column5: Nice Ski! I may be doing some ski fihing this fall at a friends cottage..Looking forward to it big time!
Great fish man!  Any pics of the homemade lure you caught it on?
Nice fish for sure!  Looks like a squirrel with blades, LOL!
Nice musky!  Congrats.
Beauty!  Skinny like a Kawarthas fish.  Maybe due to the alewife collapse in Huron?
Ya buddy!! Very nice fish, congrats
Very nice looking Ski, Congrats Tight Lines SBK
Nice ski for sure! Congrats on the 50!
3 over 50! alot of guys that have been fishing  a lot longer would love to be able to say that!!!!  good for you and the homemade lure makes it even better..  :clapping:
Awesome fish!
Congrats! I'd be thrilled just to catch 1 50" this year, let alone 3 (so far)!
Third 50+ ever or this year?  What a snake.... Is it ever skinny...  Musts felt great catching her on a home made bait too...
Sweet fish bud!!! Congratulations on your 3rd 50 -   Your bucktails look awesome too... making my own is on my to-do list for the near future.  Pete

Very cool...  I didn't LAND my first musky till I was 18...  But it's a bit easier to find information nowadays.... Learn new techniques... Etc... And it's turning out some great anglers like yourself...  Heck  We didn't even have Internet at our house growing up....
Sorry buddy but it's either exactly 50 or over. Oh, and Great fish!
Yup nice fish, and its not over 50.... haha. Great fish.
Great fish man!  I wonder how big that pig would be in about mid November
Awesome fish!!!!  All the better caught on home made tackle!  Congrats!
Beauty, congrats!
Beautiful beast....hope you can track it down in the Fall
Nice!
Very nice congrats on such a nice ski
What a beauty!
Nice fish!!  I saw the moon last night and thought someone is having fun somewhere
Wicked fish!!!  Well done!
I've never seen lamprey marks like that.
Lymphosarcoma , unfortunately becomeing more common
You will both fill out. Nice fish!
If I caught something like that my life would be complete...for a day or so

Great fish! Thats killer you got it on homemade tackle as well, congrats!!!!  To me, those don't look like lamprey marks??? All the ones I see on my fish are almost perfect circular shapes in the flesh. I've been wrong plenty of times before though, lol, so who knows???
Great fish Andrew!
Attaboy, 50's are always nice !!
Sweet  Wanna join team 7?
VHS Maybe?
